<br>
<br>
<br>
----<br>
<br>
Watching over my girlfriends shoulder as she camped the window room in Sol, her magician character Deerthorn gets into a discussion with some folks, mainly a high-and-mighty necro ... and in my oppinion, with his nose so far up his ass how could he breathe ...<br>
<br>
The necro begins to spout off paladins are worthless, not being tanks, and not resembling any form of meat shield.  Rangers were not tanks, being worthless in HP's, and magician PETS were not tanks, (can't recal his reasoning on this last one...).<br>
<br>
Of course I disagreed, and helped in the replies which my girlfriend gave.  First, PAladins ARE tanks, although not as meaty as a true Warrior tank.  They can still take a beating, and dish out some considerably damage.  Hell, when my Soulfire+FBSS combo starts hitting, I can pull consecutive 80's in double and triple attacks, and with augment, I'm raining pain =-).  Not to mention the bandaging AND healing effects.<br>
Rangers--- oh, hum now!  Rangers do some very very good damage in multiples, although in smaller numbers than a paladin (depending on weapon wielded in both cases).  Give it time, and the ranger will be aggro'ing the mob onto him, due to the massive amounts of damage they are doing.<br>
Magician PETS -- good god!  When I was near Karnor's castle last time, I was watching a magician's pet tank both a Drollvarg (yellow or black to me at 42 I -think-) and a spider, blue.  The pet was black to me.  This pet can be armored, strengthened, berserked, AND healed while its tanking.  The silly pet was pulling multiple 50's down.  I was a bit taken aback by what was going on.  A pet doing more damage than myself at some points because of its accurate 50's.  No misses, and hardly any damage smaller.<br>
<br>
Warriors -- no doubt true tanks.  I'm not going to get into what they can and can't do vs. other classes.  If you are a warrior ytou know what you can do.  <br>
<br>
<br>
So, my remark here is:<br>
<br>
The classes I listed up above ARE indeed tanks, but of different 'classes'.  The military do not use just the 'big guns' that have mega armor.  Their other tanks range from very light armored, fast maneuverability, up to heavy armor with light fire power.  Every tank has its own use and purpose.  So in the end, when this necro was telling the group how smart he was, I was guessing he either can't play other classes, has never successfully played another class, and/or was speaking through his ass.  When I log in, and can enter a group as a tank, pull mobs off of you casters, heal you in the end, and still bash the piss out of the nearest mob, you better damn well believe 'I' believe I'm a tank.  <br>
<br>
-Moonfray, War Cleric and Tank =-) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#CC9900>- </font><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis>Brell Serilis</a><font color=#CC9900> - </font><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilismeleetalk>Tome: Races and Classes </a> <font color=#CC9900> - </font><a href="http://www.brellserilis.net">Brell Serilis.net</a><font color=#CC9900> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.3.7<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  